Kiro-EULA — license summary for dev-util/kiro-bin
=================================================

*** NOTICE ***

This file is NOT an official Kiro license text. It is a summary
placeholder kept in the rato-verlay repository so that Portage's
ACCEPT_LICENSE mechanism can gate the merge of dev-util/kiro-bin on a
well-defined license token. The authoritative terms live in the AWS
agreements linked below, and in the LICENSE.txt file shipped inside
the upstream Kiro tarball.

The verbatim EULA text from the tarball will replace this file in a
follow-up commit once the tarball is unpacked. That unpacking is
deliberately deferred here because the Kiro IDE tarball is roughly
300 MB and must not be downloaded as part of repository scaffolding.

